Name: 10th Frame
MemoText:
Original version protection note:
---------------------------------
The original disk came with a dongle that must be inserted in the tape drive port. On real hardware, if you have a datasette, you can just put in a tape and press play and it will pass the protection. 
When using WinVICE just "insert" a TAP image and "start" the datasette motor to bypass the protection.
The linked NIB file is the pure original version and the D64 has been patched to work without the dongle.

Name: Carnage
MemoText:
Some tiny game bugs: 
1) In 2-Player game, when P2 has a damaged engine, his/her car is much slower than P1 with a damaged engine. 
2) Sometimes P2 with engine OK is still shown with a 'damaged engine' sprite (i.e. smoke behind the car all the time). 

And now some interesting features: 
1) If you can't finish the race within the time limit, the next race is on the same track. 
2) If you drive in such a funny way that a computer opponent can't finish the race, the opponent receives a lot of points (huh?).

MemoText:
Keyboard controls:
------------------
* = switch between board and text view 
A = advice 
B = change board or color to move 
D = demo program 
E = evaluation of game 
G = new game (or start position) 
H = help (list of features) 
I = give-away - switch to or from 
K = set alternate level for white 
L = change skill level 
M = program makes next move 
N = human plays both sides 
O = music off, or back on 
P = parameter changes 
Q = quit program and boot disk 
R = reset program 
S = stop search, movie, demo, or 'W' 
T = take back a move 
U = invert board display 
V = set random number 
W = program plays against itself 
X = replay one move 
Y = checkers movie (playback recorded game) 
Z = beeps off, or back on

Name: Evil Prince, The
MemoText:
Ok - combination follows: (I will leave out the <1> to continue the text, when you can't choose between something and the <space> before the fights ok?) When I write fight xxx, then do the following: <5> don't cast a spell, <1> attack, <^> ,<^>, repeat last three commands until dead, press <^> at the end of the fight. 
When you get low on Hitpoints press <^> to check your power, press <space> to drink a power potion and regenerate 5 Power. 

Beginning: 
<1> go to charlatan, <1> buy a potion, <1> buy a potion, <2> leave, <2> enter the pub, <1> pay a beer, <4> go to harbor, fight the ork, <1> pick it up (dagger), <3> sailor test, <1> fight 

On sea: 
<1> west, <2> sail by it 

On land: 
<2>south, <1> talk to him, <2> move on, <1> north, <3> west, <3> visit smith, <1> buy it, <1> shaman,<1> buy potion, <2> leave hut, <4>go away village, <1> go to him 

On Sea: 
<2> to the east, fight monster 

On land: 
<1>east, <2> straight, <2> east, fight 5 orks, <1> bigger mountain, <1> upwards, <1> quitely walk around, <2> canyon, <2> assist the elf, <2> clearing (bugged), <2> ..., fight the 3 zombies, <2> straight, <2> east, fight 1 ork, <1> bigger, <2> smaller 

In the cave: 
<1> west, <2> north, <1> west, <2> north, <2>east (screen is a bit bugged), <1> north --> game hangs

Name: Exile
MemoText:
1) Fly to the right until you see a grenade on the ground (it looks like a little grey ball with a dot in the middle), use the "<" Key to pick up the grenade. 

2) Fly to the right, go under the big spaceship and go down the pit/hole in the ground. You will now be at a door, which is built into the floor below your feet. Stand to the left of the door, use the ">" key to throw the grenade. The door will explode and you go inside , down the tunnel. (Remember to press the "R" key 6 times so if you die you will start at the location you pressed "R", instead of starting way back at the start.) 

3) A little 4 legged creature is blocking the path, (press runstop to crawl / fly horizontally), push the creature out the way, it will fall off the edge and hit the ground and explode. Go down and then up the passage to the left where you find the Icer (Gun) lying on the floor. Use "<" to pick it up, press "1" to activate the gun. 

4) Go down the tunnel and go into the first room on your left (by the way, when you enter this room 4 or 5 energy balls will make a buzzing sound and fly towards you, you will need to shoot these.) In this room, fly to the top centre of the room. In the pit/room above you, you should see a Blue object sitting on the floor. (Blue key) CONGRATULATIONS... 

Apparently it ain't there in the cracks he tried. Though that was 2-3 years ago now. Evidently the original disk I sent was fine, he never mentioned about the blue key being missing

Press "N"  Return to Title screen.
Press "H"  Show Hi score.
Press "F7" Leave Hi-Score Table
Press "F1" Pause on.
Press "F3" Pause off.

"Z"  Left
"X"  Right

MemoText:
Bug or programming fault (TESTED ON THE G64 AND TAP VERSIONS):
When you enter a certain area within the first level the screen scrolls up and you're able to kill the enemies inside.
When you leave the area afterwards the screen scrolls down only a bit. Now the player is caught in this area because he can't move left or right to walk around it.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
(see Bug Report in extras)
you can walk left and right you just have to be standing in line with the bottom of the barrier and you must be pixel perfect.
(it will look like you are walking through the barrier)
but unless you destroy the purple barriers (XX) *first*
you will get trapped at the point shown in the picture (2)
for the same scroll down reason.

I do not think this is a bug, but an actual part of the game.
to remember the layout of the level and avoid getting trapped.
e.g. level 2 also has an area where you can get trapped.
with an invicible wall in front of you and no scroll down.

I have managed to load level 2 sucessfully on the G64 version
but the disk level loader is very unreliable and works only 40% of the time. (thats only if you don't breathe on the keyboard or blink by accident) which is a pain in the neck because after every game over level 1 reloads. (or should i say tries to reload) and you have to start the game all over again. more work seems to have gone into the disk protection rather than function. 
no one could have ever play tested it!

for the best level loading results (99%) use the Tape Version.
tested all levels to final end screen.

approx tape counter in vice
level 1 000
level 2 033
level 3 066
level 4 092
level 5 128

INFO (not a BUG)
when you lose your 5 lives, even after loading a new level 2-3-4-5
you will find the soilder stuck on that level unable to move.
The only possible way to continue is to press RESTORE.
which will reload level 1.

bugs!! (tested on all versions G64 / TAP / IKARI / F4CG)
------
you can somtimes get trapped on the scenery.

at the end of level 1 if you approch the helicopter from the far left of the screen and stay behind the two huts (where it can't shoot you!) you will not hear the helicopter noise (WURRRRRRR).
if you stay there without moving and shoot it down with your machine gun. it will not load the next level. now move into the center of the screen and the helicopter noise will start up.
you are now stuck with nowhere to go.

press SHIFT+RETURN at player-screen to select course (A or B)


Protection Note
---------------
The original disk came with a dongle that must be inserted in the tape drive port. On real hardware, if you have a datasette, you can just put in a tape and press play and it will pass the protection. 
When using WinVICE just "insert" a TAP image and "start" the datasette motor to bypass the protection.

Name: Leaderboard Golf
MemoText:
Keyboard controls:
------------------
press SHIFT+RETURN at player-screen to select course (Original or Tournament)

Description for add on disks:
-----------------------------
To get "leaderboard tournament Disk #1" to work,
at the menu where it asks for the number of players,
insert the addon disk, then press "shift-return". 
After some loading the courses will be loaded and you
just play like usual (you can select 1 of 4 courses in
the menu).

To get the  "leaderboard executive" addon disk to
work, at the menu where it asks for the number of
players, insert the addon disk, then press
"shift-return".  After some loading course A will be
loaded by default, and you just play like usual.  If
during gameplay you wish to play course B, you simply
press "/" which takes you to the main menu.  Then
press "shift-return" and then press "B" (it says input
course at the bottom of the screen).


Original version protection note:
---------------------------------
The original disk came with a dongle that must be inserted in the tape drive port. On real hardware, if you have a datasette, you can just put in a tape and press play and it will pass the protection. 
When using WinVICE just "insert" a TAP image and "start" the datasette motor to bypass the protection.
The linked NIB file is the pure original version and the D64 has been patched to work without the dongle.

Name: Out Run Europa
V_Comment: doesn't work on real hardware (see notes)
MemoText:
The Outrun Europa game version by Emulators only works on emulators
correctly (tested in vice). On real C64s (tested on 3 x C64C, 1 x C64 BE, 1x C64-I. It crashes in the following cases:

Enable any trainer and press the f keys. Preferably f7 to freeze and simply let the game crash. you can see step by step how your car/boat/bike stops moving, then the enemies' car, then the middle street line and finally the clouds if you wait long enough.

In the Italy Cours (the one before the last one), it crashes of 9 in 10 cases if you pass "finish" it shows a colored (rainbowlike) frame whom speed you can control funnily with the f keys.

Name: Zahlen-Dreher I
MemoText:
The Universal Cracking Duo messed up the basic with protection
and made it too long with "REM's" and greetings pages.
overwriting the memory at $29a6.
lines 124,142,151 had SYS10662 ($29a6)
which crashed the game because it was jumping to part of the basic.
these lines have now been changed to read REM10662
and the memory at $29a6 is now clear incase the missing code is found.

i dont think the REMED SYS stop the program from working?.
but the game will need to be tested by someone who understands German.

also looking through the BASIC i found lines 195,196,197 are REMED?.

It is now possible to read and edit the BASIC.
incase it needs to be fixed again.

all file sizes are correct
all level files load and run ok
all pic files display 100%

file 21x tried to load file 22x that is missing.

created "22x" which boots pic "102"
created "102" took emanuel pic from the A&S game and renamed it.
then it will load "xxx" end game.

the game now ends without error.

if you boot using file "tod" (quit game over)

load any of 6 block files to start at that level

(disk 2) xy8 - 9 , x10 - 14

--------
joystick up moves tank forward
joystick down moves tank back
joystick left moves tank left
joystick right moves tank right
hold fire button and move joystick up to raise target cross
hold fire button and move joystick down to lower target cross
hold fire button and move joystick left or right to fire missile
collect the diamonds for extra fuel

Name: Sports Spectacular
MemoText:
there are two menus on the disk.
basic version (boot)
compiled version (menu)

fixed HOCKEY.

the disk contained read errors which stoped hockey from loading
this could have been the protection?

over 100 REM'ed lines had to be removed to get it working!
plus a few corrupt lines filled with garbage had to be fixed.

line 6000 was fixed
line 16143 was fixed to compare with line 16669
line 26137 removed
line 26400 was created
player goal/nets graphic added
time display added

-------------------------------------------------------------------
instructions
when the time reaches 100 and the score is a draw the game will go into sudden death overtime then whoever scores next will win.

keys while playing..
f1 - forward time 100.
f3 - reset time 0.
f5 - change screen colour.
f7 - change border colour.

in joystick mode the game quits when you press fire. 
(this is not a bug!)

Name: Lady Bug
MemoText:
Lady Bug Fixes
Too many to list but here's just a few.

Eaten Grass (all levels)
kk=xx (incorrect amounts needed to clear level)
e.g. level 12 needed 144 to finish level
with only a possible 133 to eat.

Reset Indegestion after every level.
or the levels with only 1 flower are impossible.

poke fix SUNBURN colour on completing level
using same amount carried over from last level
(or adding G4=1944 will reset amount to zero)

reset sprites on loosing life
to stop the loose all your lives bug.

Level 12
was incomplete and impossible to finish.
pokev+27,254 = puts Beetle sprite under character set
after level ends / game over was missing pokev+27,0
to put Beetle sprite back over character set.
fixed level how i think it was ment to be.

High-Score name corrupted title screen if too many letters entered.
changed to max 9 characters.

poke v,xxx   = Start Horizontal Position (Lady)
pokev+1,xxx  = Start Vertical Position (Lady)


***************************************
**      Trainer for bug testing      **
**   press up arrow to skip level.   **
***************************************

Help info.

When a beetle reaches the border of the garden it will
move up and down the far right wall.
so keep an eye them when eating grass near the right hand side wall.

you can not be killed if you are standing on a path.
but your sunburn will increase.

Name: Sammy the Slug
V_Comment: not 100%? - read Notes / is there a fix available in a later YC issue?
MemoText:
LOADING INFO...

load"sammy slug",8
run
(the screen will go blank while data is being read)
load "part2",8
run
==================================================================
PART1 lines changed.
--------------------
150 changed DATA (cabbage)
155 changed DATA (exit door)

graphics looked buggy.
==================================================================
PART2 lines changed.
--------------------
The listing did not have lines with a command to move the SLUG down.
added lines
4024 check if joystick port 2 held down.
4955 move slug down routine.

101 WA=WA+1 changed to wa=1 (level 2 somtimes started after getting killed)
197 changed ca=13 to ca>13 (ca=14 after all items collected)
198 changed ca=13 to ca>13 / removed thenWA=1 (corrupted level up)
342 changed the spacing in level graphics (the slug started over wall graphics)
497 missing a1=83 (level ended before reaching exit)
498 missing a1=83 (level ended before reaching exit)
655 ca values corrected
656 ca values corrected
657 ca values corrected
701 changed m=0 to m=3 (caused the slug to start over wall graphics)

801 added ca=0 (reset items collected)
re-numbered lines to stay in same format as all other levels
880 = 898 and changed goto16000 with goto900 (fix level up bug)
896 = 897
897 = 880
898 = 881

998 changed goto 16000 with goto 1000 (fixes level up bug)
1298 changed goto 16000 with goto 1300 (fixes level up bug)
1416 moved cabbage icon (it was impossible to collect)
1500 added a small game completed message before ending game.
51000 zero values removed clr resets all the values.

*55000 contains clr (this resets hi score on game over making it pointless)
*replaced display with bonus.
*4002 stopped bonus display -1

60151 added onwa ,goto1400 (stop game crashing when you get killed on level 14)
56000 qw=rnd(1)*14 (all levels now play if random game)
56001 added onqw goto 1200,1300,1400

###################################################################EMULATOR INFO
the AIR meter does not display when using VICE v1.17 (use bonus display)
works ok on CCS64 v3.0 Beta 1.5
###################################################################

Eat all the cabbages on each level before going to the exit.
if you walk into the exit door without the correct total needed for that level
you will eat the exit door making the level impossible to finish.
Some levels do not require you to eat every single cabbage.
but most of them do.

Name: Scramble
MemoText:
after reading the instructions you must load the last file...
load"main",8 (just press home followed by return.)

a trainer mode was added for bug testing.
press "T" on title screen. (only hit one alien for next level)

13002 c=0 added to stop game crashing on level 3 second time round.

level 3 graphics contain a SHIFT S (heart) in the listing.
this is a typing mistake.
the UDGs are only definded upto I (SHIFT - A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H,I)
the HEARTs have been changed to SHIFT D (a defined solid block).
see file "scramble" UDG DATA lines 102-299 

*HEARTs show as a space using VICE and a solid block in CCS64

Name: Computer Yehtzee
MemoText: The game doesn't calculate the top level bonuses the common way the original Yahtzee games do. Normally in Yahtzee you only get the +30 bonus when you get over a certain amount of points in the top level. In this game, you get a 30 bonus for no reason - which is kinda stupid, but that's what the author wanted, so...

Name: Bard's Tale , The
MemoText:
The tapes are labeled as such:

TAPE 1, SIDE 1: BOOT & GAME
TAPE 1, SIDE 2: CITY & DUNGEONS
TAPE 2, SIDES 1&2: ADDITIONAL DUNGEONS

I type some notes from the instructions, I think some
keys are different from the disk version:

MOVING ABOUT:
I - move forward
J - turn left
L - turn right
K - open a door

VIEWING CHARACTERS

Press the number (1-6) of the character you want to view.
In the view-character mode you have the following options:
E(quip item), T(rade item - to trade Gold, press G instead of 
item number), D(rop item), P(ool gold).
Press the Left-Arrow key in the upper-left corner of the
keyboard to leave the view character mode.

COMMANDS WHILE MOVING
C(ast a spell)
P(arty attack)
B(ard song)
N(ew order)
U(se item)
V(olume of sound on/off)
E(levate up a portal in a dungeon, if you have a levitation spell)
D(own a portal in a dungeon, if you have a levitation spell)
Left-Arrow key (pause/resume)

EDITOR
After the game on the boot cassette, there is the EDITOR program
which allows you to transfer characters between different parties
Use it for example to remove a DEAD character from a party,
replace him from a previously saved game, then resave the party.

CASSETTE COUNTER POSITIONS
You should find it useful to write down the tape counter position
of the various multi-load sections so that you can fast-forward
to them easily:

Position       Section
______        Editor
______        City Map
______        Sewers
______        Mad God's Catacombs
______        Harkyn's Castle
______        Kylearan's Amber Tower
______        Mangar's Tower

Name: Wall, The
MemoText:
the end of line 13010 was fixed due to missing print in the magazine scan
it should read POKEV+11,I (this drops a cage on you when killed).

line 63090 had goto 2 this reset the hi-score every new game ???
line 2 had hi=0 (moved hi=0 to line 0)

score & hi score graphic display corrected
any score over 9999 and the level & lives display were overwritten.

level 5 was a line short. now it has the same number as the other 4 levels.
(19001 fort=0to21)
this caused the graphics to be corrupt.
the level graphics had to be redrawn making it possible to finish.

other changes
no standing sprites over ladders.

sprites now walk on their platforms not in mid air
making them possible to jump over.

ladders now reach their platforms.

now possible to jump the spaces between platforms.

17000 level3 changed line to "PRINT F$" (level drew incorrectly)
18000 level4 was missing "PRINT D$" (end of level object)

Name: Four Crowns of Adelim, The
MemoText:
The listing was too hard to read the colours and cursor graphics
so i guessed at them.

listing also contained many errors
level value on each level was missing
on goto missing last level
getting killed on level 5 restarted game at level 4

level 1
treasure chest value needed to be reset to zero on loosing life.
or you are trapped on level.

level 2
game stoped with END command on sprite collision level 2.
also poor sprite detection on right side of screen.

level 3 / 5
expanded sprites did not reset to normal after level up.
which messed up title screen on game over.
and made level 2 impossible 2nd time round.

level 5
no character platform detection.
this caused you to walk in mid air on right-hand side of screen
above and below the crown.

Name: Slarti and Stash Space Saga , The
Treasure Max
MemoText:
http://members.aol.com/iceout0002/

-- RULES --
The flag is hidden somewhere on a 40 x 22 grid.
But traps are hidden there as well.
You start with 15 life points each level. Hitting a trap causes
it to go down by one. The game ends when it reaches zero.
Finding the flag takes you to the next level (maximum level 5).
Higher levels have more traps.

-- SCORING --
Revealing a normal spot gives 1 point and leaves a marker.
Finding the flag is worth 200xlevel points (maximum 1000).

-- HINTS AND TIPS --
The trap locations 'flash' on the screen before the level begins.

Name: Hot Tiles
MemoText:
http://minigamecomp.org.uk

-- RULES -- 
Match your tile colors with the 2x2 pattern shown on
the top-left of the screen. Tiles can be flipped
horizontally or vertically. When a match is made,
those tiles are blacked out and the time remaining
is added to your score.
